<exercise checkit-seed="0015" checkit-slug="E1" checkit-title="Linear systems, vector equations, and augmented matrices">
  <statement>
    <p>Consider the vector equation.</p>
    <me> x_{1} \left[\begin{array}{c}
1 \\
3 \\
1
\end{array}\right] + x_{2} \left[\begin{array}{c}
-1 \\
-2 \\
-1
\end{array}\right] + x_{3} \left[\begin{array}{c}
-4 \\
-7 \\
-3
\end{array}\right] + x_{4} \left[\begin{array}{c}
4 \\
4 \\
2
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \\
6 \\
3
\end{array}\right] </me>
    <ol>
      <li> Write a system of scalar equations corresponding to this vector equation. </li>
      <li> Write an augmented matrix corresponding to this vector equation. </li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <md alignment="alignat" alignat-columns=" 5 ">
          <mrow>x &amp;-&amp; y &amp;-&amp; 4 \, z &amp;+&amp; 4 \, {w} &amp;=&amp; 3</mrow>
          <mrow>3 \, x &amp;-&amp; 2 \, y &amp;-&amp; 7 \, z &amp;+&amp; 4 \, {w} &amp;=&amp; 6</mrow>
          <mrow>x &amp;-&amp; y &amp;-&amp; 3 \, z &amp;+&amp; 2 \, {w} &amp;=&amp; 3</mrow>
        </md>
      </li>
      <li>
        <me> \left[\begin{array}{cccc|c}
1 &amp; -1 &amp; -4 &amp; 4 &amp; 3 \\
3 &amp; -2 &amp; -7 &amp; 4 &amp; 6 \\
1 &amp; -1 &amp; -3 &amp; 2 &amp; 3
\end{array}\right] </me>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>

